---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Scaling Thoughts" description="About Abhinav - ML Engineer at Amazon Special Projects">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-4">
        About
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Profile section -->
      <div class="not-prose flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-8">
        <img
          src="/profile.jpg"
          alt="Abhinav"
          class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full object-cover"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">Abhinav</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            Machine Learning Engineer<br />
            Amazon Special Projects — Foundation Models & Inference
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 mt-3">
            <a href="https://github.com/abhinavsv3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-dark">GitHub</a>
            <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/abhinavsv3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-dark">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=i_dHJ6cAAAAJ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent dark:hover:text-accent-dark">Scholar</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        I build ML systems for efficient large-scale inference at Amazon's Special Projects incubator
        (Grand Challenge), where I work on foundation model optimization and production deployment.
      </p>

      <p>
        My research on prompt optimization and cross-model translation—techniques for reducing inference
        cost while maintaining reliability—was presented at the Amazon Machine Learning Conference (2025).
      </p>

      <h2>Research Background</h2>
      <p>
        My work sits at the intersection of algorithmic theory and systems engineering, shaped by
        research across multiple institutions:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>University of Florida</strong> — Master's research on graph and matrix algorithms
          for high-dimensional data visualization
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>LARCA, Universitat Politècnica de Catalunya (Barcelona)</strong> — Research on
          relational algorithms and computational learning theory with Prof. Ricard Gavaldà
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tokyo City University</strong> — Exchange research on algorithmic efficiency
          under hardware constraints with Prof. Takamichi Hirata
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Institute of Mathematical Sciences (Chennai)</strong> — Early research exposure
          in computational modeling and formal methods
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        I completed my undergraduate studies at <strong>SASTRA University</strong>, India.
      </p>

      <h2>This Blog</h2>
      <p>
        Scaling Thoughts covers the engineering behind production ML: inference optimization,
        foundation model deployment, and the architectural decisions that make large-scale
        systems work. I write to document what I learn and share what I find useful.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800" />

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        Opinions expressed here are my own and do not represent my employer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
